==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Moravian
<hw>Mo*ra"vi*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining
to Moravia, or to the United Brethren. See <er>Moravian</er>,
<pos>n.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Moravian</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Moravian
<hw>Mo*ra"vi*an</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Eccl. Hist.)</fld> <def>One of
a religious sect called the <membof>United Brethren</membof> (an
offshoot of the Hussites in Bohemia), which formed a separate church of
Moravia, a northern district of Austria, about the middle of the 15th
century. After being nearly extirpated by persecution, the society,
under the name of <membof>The Renewed Church of the United
Brethren</membof>, was reestablished in 1722-35 on the estates of
<person>Count Zinzendorf</person> in Saxony. Called also
<altname>Herrnhuter</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Moravianism</ent>⟦br⟧
